In Create_first_job.md and Create_second_job(private_repo) we build manually 

To automate this process we use triggers which can configured using triggers options we are going to learn 3 types of triggers
1) Webhooks
2) Pollscm
3) build periodically 

Using Webhooks:-
(steps to be done in github)
1) Go to repo settings which are used in the first job or second job 
2) you wil see option webhook 
3) Add webhook by adding payloadurl( ipaddr:8080/github-webhook)
(steps to be done in jenkins)
1) go to job and configuire trggers by selecting webhooks
2)then save 

observations:- 
1) github talks to jenkins 
2) new commits automatically pushed to pipeline 


